headline.main: ALLIES POUND FOE; Warships and Relays of Planes Striking at the New Invasion Fleet NO ADVANCE ON LAND Counter-Attacks Go On 'Satisfactorily,' but the Outlook Is Still Grave

lead_paragraph: LONDON, Tuesday, March 3 -Dispatches from Batavia said today that a huge new Japanese invasion armada was bearing down upon Java and was being met by continuous relays of United States Flying Fortresses and other United Nations bombers.
abstract: New Jap invasion fleet reptd nearing Java
